body.name: Modern 6 Drawer Wood Dresser, Wood Lateral Chest of Drawers Storage Organizer with Wide Drawers & Metal Gold Handles for Bedroom, Living Room, Hallway, Entryway
deliveryMessages: Or fastest delivery Friday, February 16. Order within 20 hrs 1 min
features: 🟠Versatile Storage Solution: This 6-Drawer Chest of Drawers offers generous storage capacity with a unique design. The drawers are thoughtfully distributed, with three on the left side and three on the right, allowing you to organize and separate your items conveniently.

🟡Color and Style Options: You can choose between two elegant colors, black and white, to match your home decor. Additionally, this cabinet is available in two styles: the high-legged version, which adds a touch of sophistication to your space, and the footless version for a sleek and minimalist look.

🔵Premium Gold Accents: The cabinet is adorned with stylish gold handles and gold feet, adding a touch of luxury to its overall appearance. These accents enhance the cabinet's aesthetics and make it stand out in any room.

🟢Durable and Stable Construction: Built to last, this chest of drawers features a stable and sturdy structure that ensures years of reliable use. Crafted from eco-friendly materials, it not only contributes to sustainability but also offers exceptional durability. The robust design can withstand the test of time and daily use without wobbling or instability.

🟣Functional and Space-Saving: The chest's vertical layout optimizes your floor space, making it an excellent choice for smaller rooms or apartments. The six drawers offer an efficient way to keep your belongings organized, allowing you to easily find what you need. Whether in the bedroom, living room, or hallway, this chest of drawers adds both functionality and style to your living space.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very pleased with this dresser but…
reviews.reviewText: I’m very happy with this dresser. The only real complaint I have is that if you have baseboards, you can’t really use the wall anchors without tipping the dresser back, which is probably about as unsafe as not having wall anchors. I put the dresser in my kids’ room but fortunately they’re old enough to understand why they can’t climb on it. The drawers are a bit flimsy and probably wouldn’t hold very many adult-sized clothing items because they’re not very deep but they’re perfect for my kids’ clothes. It looks nice and wasn’t too difficult to assemble alone.
